<p><b>What is social learning theory Bandura 1965?</b> The SLT states that in response to observation, imitation, and modeling, learning can occur even without changing behavior (Bandura, 1965). This article introduces Bandura's social learning theory and explores key concepts, real-life examples, and some fascinating experiments.</p>